\begin_layout Section
Wireless Mesh Networks
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Wireless Mesh Networks or WMN is a type wireless access network that combine
 the Wireless Local Area Networks (WLANs) and Mobile Ad hoc Networks (MANET).
 WMN consists of two kinds one is client-based mesh networks while the other
 is infrastructure-based mesh networks.
 Client based allows end nodes such as transceivers, cellphones or laptops
 to participate in relaying data in a network, while infrastructure based
 prohibits this and uses a backbone network that is responsible for relaying.
 More and more application in WMN are emerging like communication, first
 response systems, and loacalization.
 In localization, most algorithm are for WLANs and MANETs which does not
 utilize the advantages of WMN which is the ability of each end node to
 communicate.
 
