\begin_layout Section
Problem Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Currently UP Bike Share intends to execute everything manually, i.e., rider
 registration, bike monitoring and quality control.
 In doing so they may not be able to check whether every rider is adhering
 to the rules that they have lain down, therefore there is no assurance
 that every bike is being used exclusively inside campus premises.
 There have been reports of bike sightings outside the vicinity of UP Diliman,
 e.g., Katipunan, Maginhawa, etc.
 They have also lost a few bikes since they have started, and this scenario
 can go on if no device is made to support their cause and strictly implement
 their rules.
 By creating a tech that could support their advocacy by tracking every
 bike in their arsenal, they would be able to track down the violators and
 give them a proper sanction, while ensuring that every bike and rider is
 kept safe and unharmed, leading towards a better biking community for UP
 Diliman.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Objectives
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We intend to create an automated consolidating unit using a wireless mesh
 network that could monitor the whereabouts of the bike and the information
 of the rider that currently rented the bike.
 The bike share initiative intends to expand as the years progress, therefore
 that would mean more bikes, consequently more devices, since each bike
 would need its own tech, this is why the materials to be used to fabricate
 the device should be cheap.
 There is an initial plan that the tech could be powered by the pedaling
 motion of the biker, this can only be done if the device isn’t too power
 hungry.
 Riders wouldn’t like the idea of exerting too much effort in biking and
 keeping the device powered, that is why the device must need only a small
 amount of energy to power it.
 The device should have a way to monitor the whereabouts of the bikes accurately
 so that the location of each bike can be retrieved if or when needed.
\end_layout

