\begin_layout Chapter
Methodology
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Our proposed method uses the Ring Overlapping Localization (ROL) which is
 based on Sub-Partial Range Aware distance measurement (SPRA).
 ROL is an algorithm developed from trilateration.
 Since trilaterion uses overlapping circles created using the RSSI of a
 target node and a base station, it will encounter errors brought by interferenc
es.
 ROL tries to improve trilateration by using rings that to localize a target,
 and to obtain the radii of the rings we are going to use SPRA measurement
 which maps a particular RSSI to a particular range of distance.
\end_layout

